<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/937.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Honduran Legation</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Aide Memoire.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Honduras</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-26"><hi rend="italic">December 26,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The minister of Honduras presents his compliments to his excellency the
                            Secretary of State and has the honor to inform him <pb facs="0376" n="294" xml:id="pg_294"/> that Gens. Manuel Bonilla and Lee
                            Christmas, leaders of the Honduran revolutionists, left New Orleans on
                            Friday the 23d and probably on board the steamship <hi rend="italic">Hornet.</hi></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>